The authorities treated me as if I were an old gossip, a troublemaker, a whiner.
They want us to accept what they say and keep quiet.
"But it's not normal that there are so many irregularities and omissions," she said.
When President Pena Nieto receives his scarf on Saturday, it will come with a heavy responsibility.
