Although rocket fire from Gaza has killed about 30 Israelis since 2004, Israel has been spared suicide bombings, thanks in part to the separation barrier that encroaches on the West Bank, the main piece of what could be a Palestinian state, and protects Jewish settlements that continue to expand despite their illegality under international law.
Netanyahu, whose Likud party has merged with an even more hawkish party, that of leader Avigdor Lieberman in the run-up to the Jan. 22 election, has the upper hand.
Why coddle these damn Palestinians by giving them a state?
If they ruled the West Bank, wouldn't they launch rockets, as their compatriots did in Gaza?
It is best to keep them behind this wall and hit them as soon as they stick their heads out.
