Israel's defense budget is larger than that of its four Arab neighbors combined.
Starting a war with the local superpower will not help the new Arab governments fix their economies.
Morsi has worked with Barack Obama to secure a ceasefire, which bodes well -- and could mark the beginning of something.
Israelis should also think about the future.
With the rest of the Arab world becoming more democratic, stripping Palestinians of their right to self-determination could create a powder keg that is bound to explode one day in the Israeli-occupied territories — much like the bus that exploded in Tel Aviv this week.
